net.objectof.impl.spring

Class ISpringContext<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.objectof.impl.spring.ISpringContext<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Context<T>, Named, org.springframework.beans.factory.BeanFactory

    public class ISpringContext<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Context<T>, org.springframework.beans.factory.BeanFactory
    Provides an object that is both a Spring BeanFactory and an objectof Context. Within the definition of objectof's Context contracts:
    • This can be both a factory and a domain.
    • forName will throw an IllegalArgumentException when a member name isn't recognized.
    • This is a reified context. The context holds a runtime reference to the generic class and a ClassCastException will be thrown if requesting a Bean that is not of this Instance's reified type.
    Author:
    jdh

        Specified by:
        forName in interface Context<T>
        Parameters:
        aName - A name identifying the singleton or a type of instance to return.
        Returns:
        An object for aComponentName or null. This interface doesn't specify any constraints on the object that is returned for each invocation: i.e. there is no requirement that the same object or null or a different object will be returned for repeated calls to this even when the same name is specified.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - When aName is not defined or defines an object that is not a subclass of this Context's (reified) type. Null will not be returned for unknown names and the object will [probably?] be a subclass of getComponentPeer().
